---
layout: recipe
title: "Toffee (Connie)"
author: "Connie"
---

### Ingredients

1 cup Heavy Cream  
½ cup Cream  
½ cup Brown Sugar, packed  
1 cup Wh. Sugar  
¾ cup Lily Wh. Corn Syrup  
Dash Salt  
½ tsp. Vanilla  
2 tbsp. Butter  

### Instructions

In a heavy saucepan, mix ¾ cup of the cream mixture with sugar, syrup, and salt.  
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring to dissolve the sugar.  
Cook to soft ball stage (234°F), stirring occasionally.  
Very slowly add the rest of the cream so the syrup continues to boil.  
Cook, stirring occasionally, to firm ball stage (244°F).  
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and butter.  
Place in a buttered pan.
